1
00:00:00,050 --> 00:00:01,450
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,450 --> 00:00:02,750
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:05,083 --> 00:00:07,850
You said you had plans.
Your plans were with Manager Seo?

4
00:00:08,150 --> 00:00:10,550
What? Yes...

5
00:00:11,450 --> 00:00:13,350
Manager Seo gave me a ride home.

6
00:00:15,983 --> 00:00:17,750
What are you doing here, Gyeol?

7
00:00:19,250 --> 00:00:20,550
Why are you at Ms. Cho Eun Ae's house?

8
00:00:21,250 --> 00:00:22,250
I live here.

9
00:00:23,950 --> 00:00:27,383
What? What did you just say?

10
00:00:27,750 --> 00:00:28,950
Exactly what you heard.

11
00:00:29,783 --> 00:00:31,350
I live in the same house
as Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

12
00:00:35,150 --> 00:00:36,283
I'm sorry, Manager.

13
00:00:36,483 --> 00:00:39,450
Team Manager Ko moved in
without knowing this was my house,

14
00:00:39,450 --> 00:00:40,483
and I only found out afterward...

15
00:00:40,750 --> 00:00:42,583
Why are you apologizing, Ms. Cho Eun Ae?

16
00:00:45,850 --> 00:00:49,450
Was I supposed to tell you where I live?

17
00:00:50,450 --> 00:00:51,450
Gyeol.

18
00:00:51,850 --> 00:00:52,850
Team Manager.

19
00:00:53,083 --> 00:00:54,750
Considering you came all the way here
this late,

20
00:00:55,683 --> 00:00:58,683
it seems like you already know everything.
Am I wrong?

21
00:01:01,183 --> 00:01:02,183
Stop it!

22
00:01:12,750 --> 00:01:14,083
What did you come here to confirm?

23
00:01:15,050 --> 00:01:16,050
Let's go.

24
00:01:18,683 --> 00:01:21,250
You think I came here
knowing you two live together?

25
00:01:22,350 --> 00:01:24,850
I just had a meeting with Ms. Cho Eun Ae,

26
00:01:25,483 --> 00:01:27,150
and since it got late,
I was giving her a ride home.

27
00:01:28,550 --> 00:01:31,283
What's wrong with that?
Did I do something wrong?

28
00:01:31,450 --> 00:01:32,750
No, Manager.

29
00:01:33,150 --> 00:01:34,683
Thank you very much for the ride...

30
00:01:34,683 --> 00:01:36,050
Ms. Cho Eun Ae, could you step aside?

31
00:01:37,283 --> 00:01:38,283
Sorry?

32
00:01:38,450 --> 00:01:39,850
I said step aside.

33
00:01:39,850 --> 00:01:41,850
Can't you see I'm talking to him
right now?

34
00:01:41,850 --> 00:01:42,850
Seo Seung Ri.

35
00:01:43,950 --> 00:01:46,883
Ms. Cho Eun Ae, take Gyeol inside.

36
00:01:47,250 --> 00:01:50,450
Okay. Team Manager, let's go inside.

37
00:01:50,850 --> 00:01:53,450
What does she mean to you
that you're acting like this?

38
00:01:54,150 --> 00:01:55,783
How can you do this to me?

39
00:01:56,383 --> 00:01:57,650
That's enough, Seo Seung Ri.

40
00:01:58,150 --> 00:02:00,883
How much longer am I supposed to put up
with your tantrums?

41
00:02:02,250 --> 00:02:03,950
Are you done talking?

42
00:02:05,050 --> 00:02:06,883
How much longer
are you going to keep this up?

43
00:02:07,850 --> 00:02:09,183
If you left,
then you should've stayed gone.

44
00:02:10,150 --> 00:02:11,950
Why come back
and stir up Seung Ri's feelings?

45
00:02:16,050 --> 00:02:19,383
You think I stirred up her feelings?
Seriously?

46
00:02:20,350 --> 00:02:21,950
- You jerk...
- What's wrong with you two?

47
00:02:22,450 --> 00:02:24,550
Please stop.

48
00:02:44,750 --> 00:02:45,750
Seung Ri.

49
00:02:47,250 --> 00:02:48,250
Are you okay?

50
00:02:49,483 --> 00:02:51,850
I'm fine. Don't worry about me.

51
00:03:04,350 --> 00:03:07,483
Do you think she really knew
and still gave me a ride home?

52
00:03:08,150 --> 00:03:09,983
Because she wanted to see for herself?

53
00:03:15,050 --> 00:03:18,550
I think she likes you a lot more than...

54
00:03:18,850 --> 00:03:20,150
Don't worry too much.

55
00:03:21,183 --> 00:03:23,683
In a few months,
it'll all sort itself out naturally.

56
00:03:24,483 --> 00:03:27,850
I'm leaving, and I'm never coming back.

57
00:03:30,250 --> 00:03:33,650
You're really leaving?

58
00:03:35,450 --> 00:03:38,250
Then what about me?

59
00:03:40,283 --> 00:03:41,283
What?

60
00:03:42,583 --> 00:03:46,750
What am I supposed to do after you leave?

61
00:03:49,850 --> 00:03:50,850
No, I mean...

62
00:03:52,150 --> 00:03:55,650
What happens to Our Happy Home?

63
00:03:56,750 --> 00:03:58,783
Regardless of the competition results,

64
00:03:58,783 --> 00:04:01,650
we promised
we'd build a good home together.

65
00:04:14,083 --> 00:04:15,850
- Eun Hyeong.
- Eun Ae.

66
00:04:16,683 --> 00:04:18,550
- Hello.
- Hello.

67
00:04:20,350 --> 00:04:22,450
What brings you here?
And what's with that suitcase?

68
00:04:22,850 --> 00:04:23,850
I'll explain later.

69
00:04:24,750 --> 00:04:26,350
Are Mom and Dad asleep?

70
00:04:26,750 --> 00:04:29,950
No. They just went into their room,
so they're probably still awake.

71
00:04:29,983 --> 00:04:30,983
Okay.

72
00:04:33,250 --> 00:04:35,083
What is it, Eun Hyeong? What's going on?

73
00:04:35,083 --> 00:04:36,083
Eun Ae.

74
00:04:37,050 --> 00:04:40,550
I need to have a private conversation
with Mom and Dad.

75
00:04:41,650 --> 00:04:44,050
I'm sorry, but could you stay out here
a little longer?

76
00:04:44,983 --> 00:04:47,350
What? Okay.

77
00:04:51,350 --> 00:04:52,383
What's going on now?

78
00:04:55,783 --> 00:04:57,983
What did you just say?

79
00:04:59,150 --> 00:05:00,250
You got divorced?

80
00:05:01,950 --> 00:05:06,250
We filed our uncontested divorce papers
at the court today.

81
00:05:06,950 --> 00:05:10,350
Cho Eun Hyeong, where did this divorce
come from all of a sudden?

82
00:05:11,083 --> 00:05:12,850
I'm so sorry, Mom, Dad.

83
00:05:13,483 --> 00:05:15,050
My goodness.

84
00:05:15,550 --> 00:05:16,783
What on earth is going on?

85
00:05:17,650 --> 00:05:20,550
Then all this time,
Ji Seon wasn't on a business trip?

86
00:05:23,050 --> 00:05:26,050
Tell us everything from the beginning.
What happened?

87
00:05:26,583 --> 00:05:27,583
Come on.

88
00:05:28,150 --> 00:05:31,250
No, honey. Let's go to Eun Hyeong's house.

89
00:05:31,250 --> 00:05:33,250
We need to talk this through
with Ji Seon together.

90
00:05:33,683 --> 00:05:34,683
Get up. Hurry.

91
00:05:34,983 --> 00:05:35,983
Ji Seon...

92
00:05:37,850 --> 00:05:39,083
She left.

93
00:05:41,783 --> 00:05:42,783
And...

94
00:05:43,850 --> 00:05:46,683
that house is gone too, Mom.

95
00:05:48,850 --> 00:05:53,283
What? What are you talking about?

96
00:05:53,950 --> 00:05:56,150
What do you mean, the house is gone?

97
00:05:56,983 --> 00:05:59,450
Explain. What do you mean?

98
00:06:04,583 --> 00:06:05,583
An investment scam?

99
00:06:06,150 --> 00:06:08,550
How could Ji Seon invest money
when she didn't have any?

100
00:06:08,850 --> 00:06:11,650
So what happened? How much did you lose?

101
00:06:12,250 --> 00:06:13,583
Everything we had.

102
00:06:14,450 --> 00:06:16,650
All 50,000 dollars she invested
from our deposit.

103
00:06:17,350 --> 00:06:19,250
What?

104
00:06:21,050 --> 00:06:23,683
We had to move out immediately,

105
00:06:23,883 --> 00:06:25,883
so I just packed up
my and Bit Na's belongings and left.

106
00:06:27,750 --> 00:06:28,783
Then what about Ji Seon?

107
00:06:29,650 --> 00:06:31,850
I don't know.
She won't tell me where she's staying.

108
00:06:33,183 --> 00:06:36,150
What are we going to do, honey?

109
00:06:36,650 --> 00:06:37,650
Mom.

110
00:06:38,350 --> 00:06:40,250
I really...

111
00:06:40,250 --> 00:06:41,650
- What are we going to do?
- I understand...

112
00:06:41,650 --> 00:06:44,250
that you had to move out immediately
because of the scam.

113
00:06:44,850 --> 00:06:46,283
But how could you get a divorce?

114
00:06:47,383 --> 00:06:50,083
Dad, I didn't want a divorce either.

115
00:06:50,083 --> 00:06:52,083
I tried everything not to get divorced.

116
00:06:52,883 --> 00:06:55,850
But Ji Seon can't forgive herself.

117
00:06:56,450 --> 00:06:58,650
She said she'd pay back
all the debt herself,

118
00:06:58,650 --> 00:07:00,350
and she kept begging me to divorce her.

119
00:07:00,650 --> 00:07:02,783
I just couldn't talk her out of it.

120
00:07:03,850 --> 00:07:04,850
My goodness.

121
00:07:05,950 --> 00:07:07,350
And all this time,

122
00:07:07,650 --> 00:07:10,350
Bit Na's been waiting for her mom,
without even knowing what's going on?

123
00:07:11,350 --> 00:07:12,983
I'm so sorry, Mom, Dad.

124
00:07:14,283 --> 00:07:16,950
Please take care of Bit Na
until I can find even a studio apartment.

125
00:07:17,350 --> 00:07:18,450
Then I'll get going.

126
00:07:18,450 --> 00:07:21,583
Where are you going at this hour?
You don't even have anywhere to go.

127
00:07:22,483 --> 00:07:23,850
I'll try to find somewhere,

128
00:07:24,050 --> 00:07:25,850
even a sauna, where I can sleep tonight.

129
00:07:28,183 --> 00:07:29,950
- Dad!
- Bit Na!

130
00:07:30,950 --> 00:07:31,950
Bit Na.

131
00:07:32,450 --> 00:07:35,050
Did you come to get me, Dad? Where's Mom?

132
00:07:36,950 --> 00:07:39,183
Her business trip isn't over yet.

133
00:07:39,550 --> 00:07:42,650
Still?
It's been more than seven nights already.

134
00:07:48,750 --> 00:07:51,950
If you don't mind,

135
00:07:53,350 --> 00:07:55,850
would you spend the night with me tonight?

136
00:07:59,883 --> 00:08:00,983
I'm home.

137
00:08:04,350 --> 00:08:06,283
What's wrong? Did something happen?

138
00:08:10,283 --> 00:08:11,350
No way.

139
00:08:12,650 --> 00:08:15,683
How could something like this happen
to Eun Hyeong?

140
00:08:15,750 --> 00:08:16,850
I know.

141
00:08:17,450 --> 00:08:20,050
As if me alone wasn't enough,
now Eun Hyeong too.

142
00:08:20,583 --> 00:08:22,983
I thought our family
was finally starting to stabilize.

143
00:08:24,550 --> 00:08:26,250
Mom must be devastated.

144
00:08:26,650 --> 00:08:29,250
Mom is one thing, but what about Bit Na?

145
00:08:29,950 --> 00:08:31,750
She's been waiting for her mom every day.

146
00:08:40,350 --> 00:08:41,750
Why did you go there?

147
00:08:42,350 --> 00:08:43,650
What were you hoping to find?

148
00:08:43,950 --> 00:08:45,450
I wanted to see for myself...

149
00:08:46,283 --> 00:08:49,983
whether what I saw was real
or just a misunderstanding.

150
00:08:50,050 --> 00:08:51,683
And what do you gain from that?

151
00:08:53,050 --> 00:08:54,783
It's not just the two of them
living there.

152
00:08:56,650 --> 00:08:59,983
He didn't move in knowing that.
It just happened by chance.

153
00:09:00,350 --> 00:09:03,983
Wait. You're relieved
that they don't live alone together?

154
00:09:04,450 --> 00:09:05,450
Is that what you mean?

155
00:09:05,950 --> 00:09:08,783
They're just temporarily excited...

156
00:09:08,783 --> 00:09:10,650
by unfamiliar feelings.

157
00:09:11,250 --> 00:09:14,850
Once Gyeol leaves, it'll be over
between him and Ms. Cho Eun Ae.

158
00:09:14,950 --> 00:09:17,583
And what about you? It won't be over
for you too even after he leaves?

159
00:09:19,550 --> 00:09:22,650
Even after things have come this far,
you still can't give up?

160
00:09:22,783 --> 00:09:25,150
You should ask yourself that question,
Chief Ko.

161
00:09:25,750 --> 00:09:28,883
Why are you still here by my side
in a situation like this?

162
00:09:29,550 --> 00:09:30,550
Seo Seung Ri.

163
00:09:32,350 --> 00:09:33,450
I'll get going.

164
00:09:34,983 --> 00:09:36,650
Stay right there.
I'm not finished talking.

165
00:09:40,150 --> 00:09:42,783
I can't do this anymore.

166
00:09:43,983 --> 00:09:47,350
I can't keep watching you hurt yourself,
fall apart,

167
00:09:48,983 --> 00:09:50,050
and make yourself miserable.

168
00:09:52,250 --> 00:09:54,350
This isn't how I planned
to give it to you.

169
00:10:01,850 --> 00:10:04,883
I'm really fine. You sleep on the bed.

170
00:10:05,583 --> 00:10:06,583
No, I can't.

171
00:10:06,950 --> 00:10:09,483
I'm already imposing enough
by staying in your room for the night.

172
00:10:10,150 --> 00:10:11,750
I can't take the bed too.

173
00:10:11,850 --> 00:10:14,950
My room?
This used to be your room, big bro.

174
00:10:14,950 --> 00:10:16,850
I'm only borrowing it for a few months.

175
00:10:18,250 --> 00:10:19,250
Big bro?

176
00:10:19,683 --> 00:10:22,550
Yes. You seem older than me.

177
00:10:23,683 --> 00:10:25,750
Though I may look older
than I actually am,

178
00:10:26,050 --> 00:10:28,750
I don't think I'm that much older.

179
00:10:29,483 --> 00:10:32,650
Still, since you're calling me big bro,
then I'll call you little bro.

180
00:10:33,650 --> 00:10:34,983
Call me whatever you're comfortable with.

181
00:10:35,983 --> 00:10:37,050
Now please sleep on the bed.

182
00:10:37,250 --> 00:10:39,883
Little bro, sleep is a process...

183
00:10:40,583 --> 00:10:44,583
through which physical recovery
and mental peace occur simultaneously.

184
00:10:45,650 --> 00:10:47,750
Right now,
I need to offset my emotional pain...

185
00:10:47,750 --> 00:10:51,250
through physical discomfort,
so just do as I say.

186
00:10:51,250 --> 00:10:54,150
Big bro, that's a wonderful sentiment.

187
00:10:54,550 --> 00:10:57,683
But this isn't for your sake.
It's for mine.

188
00:10:57,950 --> 00:11:01,050
If I feel guilty, then tonight,
I won't get any physical rest...

189
00:11:02,550 --> 00:11:03,550
Come in.

190
00:11:05,883 --> 00:11:08,450
You two,
I've been trying to sleep for 30 minutes,

191
00:11:08,450 --> 00:11:11,650
but you won't stop talking.

192
00:11:11,783 --> 00:11:14,450
Please help me out here so I can sleep.

193
00:11:15,050 --> 00:11:16,650
See? That's why you should...

194
00:11:17,250 --> 00:11:19,083
That's why you should...

195
00:11:19,650 --> 00:11:22,250
Enough. Just do what I say.

196
00:11:23,150 --> 00:11:24,850
- Rock, paper, scissors.
- Rock, paper, scissors.

197
00:11:25,550 --> 00:11:27,850
Big bro, you should just sleep on the bed.

198
00:11:27,850 --> 00:11:29,650
No, you should.

199
00:11:29,650 --> 00:11:32,550
No, I'm really fine.

200
00:11:32,550 --> 00:11:35,750
Little Bro, please.
Please sleep on the bed.

201
00:11:37,183 --> 00:11:38,283
Just lie down.

202
00:11:38,750 --> 00:11:40,950
What's going to change
by sitting there staring into space?

203
00:11:43,550 --> 00:11:44,550
Honey.

204
00:11:46,150 --> 00:11:47,283
This isn't a dream, is it?

205
00:11:48,450 --> 00:11:50,350
Did this really happen to our family?

206
00:11:54,083 --> 00:11:55,550
I still can't believe it myself.

207
00:11:56,550 --> 00:11:57,550
I mean...

208
00:11:58,450 --> 00:12:01,683
No matter how guilty she feels
about what she did,

209
00:12:03,050 --> 00:12:04,450
how could she even think
about giving up Bit Na?

210
00:12:09,750 --> 00:12:11,350
I think it's because of me.

211
00:12:13,150 --> 00:12:16,750
If I hadn't said those things back then...

212
00:12:17,950 --> 00:12:20,850
What do you mean? What did you say?

213
00:12:23,550 --> 00:12:25,950
When I ran away from home,

214
00:12:28,050 --> 00:12:31,250
I met Ji Seon after deciding
to divorce you.

215
00:12:33,350 --> 00:12:34,350
Back then, I told her...

216
00:12:36,150 --> 00:12:39,850
Eun Hyeong takes after his dad,

217
00:12:40,750 --> 00:12:44,450
so he may never change much
from the way he is now.

218
00:12:46,083 --> 00:12:48,950
If you're worried about Bit Na, don't be.

219
00:12:49,483 --> 00:12:52,283
You can still be her mother
even after a divorce.

220
00:12:53,550 --> 00:12:55,950
No matter who raises her,

221
00:12:56,650 --> 00:12:58,183
it'll work out as long as
each parent fulfills their role.

222
00:12:58,750 --> 00:13:02,250
What? How could you say
something like that to her?

223
00:13:02,483 --> 00:13:03,850
I meant it at the time.

224
00:13:05,483 --> 00:13:07,450
I was so disappointed in you,

225
00:13:08,850 --> 00:13:12,383
and I thought Eun Hyeong
would be no better than you.

226
00:13:12,583 --> 00:13:13,850
Even so,

227
00:13:15,483 --> 00:13:19,150
how could you say she could still be
a mother after a divorce...

228
00:13:19,450 --> 00:13:21,583
Mom...

229
00:13:21,583 --> 00:13:22,983
There.

230
00:13:24,750 --> 00:13:26,950
She must be dreaming about her mom.

231
00:13:28,350 --> 00:13:29,350
Mom.

232
00:13:33,250 --> 00:13:34,550
My goodness.

233
00:13:35,350 --> 00:13:41,583
<i>On the way to work</i>

234
00:13:43,150 --> 00:13:46,683
<i>White wild roses</i>

235
00:13:48,550 --> 00:13:54,950
<i>The white petals</i>

236
00:13:55,850 --> 00:13:58,783
<i>Taste good</i>

237
00:14:01,583 --> 00:14:04,350
<i>When you're hungry</i>

238
00:14:05,383 --> 00:14:08,583
How do you know that song, "Wild Rose?"

239
00:14:09,550 --> 00:14:11,850
Young people these days
don't usually know it.

240
00:14:12,850 --> 00:14:15,083
My mom always sang it to me as a lullaby.

241
00:14:16,350 --> 00:14:18,083
How do you know that song, Team Manager?

242
00:14:19,550 --> 00:14:23,050
My grandma used to sing it to me
as a lullaby.

243
00:14:23,650 --> 00:14:30,250
<i>The white petals taste good</i>

244
00:14:36,550 --> 00:14:37,750
Why are you coming down from upstairs?

245
00:14:37,883 --> 00:14:39,350
Honey.

246
00:14:39,650 --> 00:14:41,583
I don't think Min Ho came home last night.

247
00:14:42,083 --> 00:14:43,650
It doesn't look like
he went jogging either.

248
00:14:43,850 --> 00:14:45,950
And the bed sheets are untouched.

249
00:14:46,483 --> 00:14:47,850
Did Min Ho stay out all night?

250
00:14:48,250 --> 00:14:51,150
Sorry? No, not exactly.

251
00:14:51,150 --> 00:14:54,050
He told me he was working late...

252
00:14:54,050 --> 00:14:56,450
because of the second round.
I just forgot.

253
00:14:56,650 --> 00:15:00,250
Really?
You didn't mention anything last night...

254
00:15:02,450 --> 00:15:05,250
No, wait. You did.

255
00:15:05,950 --> 00:15:06,950
There are things you shouldn't forget.

256
00:15:07,650 --> 00:15:10,750
And Min Ho is really fired up these days.

257
00:15:11,283 --> 00:15:14,250
I think he'll do great
in the second round too.

258
00:15:15,250 --> 00:15:17,850
Really?
It's good that he's giving it his best.

259
00:15:18,250 --> 00:15:19,750
Come on. Let's eat breakfast.

260
00:15:20,083 --> 00:15:21,583
- Yes.
- Yes, Father.

261
00:15:21,883 --> 00:15:24,450
Honey, you go in first.

262
00:15:24,450 --> 00:15:26,250
I'm going to call Min Ho.

263
00:15:26,683 --> 00:15:27,983
Okay. Right, honey.

264
00:15:28,750 --> 00:15:32,150
I think
I'll stop by Seung Ri's place today.

265
00:15:32,883 --> 00:15:33,883
Again? Why?

266
00:15:34,550 --> 00:15:37,650
Mr. Seo is the only one
who can figure out the safe's password.

267
00:15:38,050 --> 00:15:39,583
I have to do whatever it takes.

268
00:15:40,183 --> 00:15:42,783
You're really going through a lot,
Crystal.

269
00:15:43,083 --> 00:15:44,850
(Kangsu Construction)

270
00:15:52,783 --> 00:15:53,783
Hi, Dad.

271
00:15:55,550 --> 00:15:57,950
It got too late, so I slept at the office.

272
00:15:59,250 --> 00:16:00,450
Don't worry.

273
00:16:06,683 --> 00:16:08,783
I can't do this anymore.

274
00:16:10,050 --> 00:16:13,550
I can't keep watching you
hurt yourself, fall apart,

275
00:16:15,083 --> 00:16:16,150
and make yourself miserable.

276
00:16:18,450 --> 00:16:20,550
This isn't how I planned
to give it to you.

277
00:16:24,850 --> 00:16:25,850
Min Ho.

278
00:16:28,483 --> 00:16:31,650
When I was little, I saw you hit Gyeol.

279
00:16:33,383 --> 00:16:36,550
That's one of the reasons
I came to dislike you.

280
00:16:40,483 --> 00:16:42,350
Never lay a hand on Gyeol again.

281
00:16:43,550 --> 00:16:44,850
I won't forgive you for that.

282
00:17:16,850 --> 00:17:19,850
You sure eat well
when your dad's around, Bit Na.

283
00:17:21,683 --> 00:17:22,883
Thank you for the meal.

284
00:17:23,450 --> 00:17:26,250
Bit Na, brush your teeth
and get ready for kindergarten.

285
00:17:26,283 --> 00:17:29,183
Okay. I'm going to kindergarten
with you today, Dad.

286
00:17:31,850 --> 00:17:33,350
Were you comfortable last night?

287
00:17:33,350 --> 00:17:34,783
Absolutely.

288
00:17:35,350 --> 00:17:37,150
And if you don't mind,

289
00:17:37,483 --> 00:17:40,950
why don't you just stay here with me
instead of looking for another place?

290
00:17:41,383 --> 00:17:43,083
No, I could never do that.

291
00:17:43,650 --> 00:17:45,783
I'll find a room and move out today.

292
00:17:47,050 --> 00:17:50,150
Bit Na loves having her dad around.
Just stay.

293
00:17:50,950 --> 00:17:52,450
Are you really okay with that,
Team Manager Ko?

294
00:17:52,450 --> 00:17:54,850
Of course.
I'll be leaving in a few months anyway.

295
00:17:55,650 --> 00:17:57,450
I'll get going now.
Thank you for the meal.

296
00:17:58,450 --> 00:18:00,050
Me too. Thanks for the meal, Mom.

297
00:18:00,383 --> 00:18:02,283
Okay. Get ready and head to work.

298
00:18:06,650 --> 00:18:09,550
What are you going to do now?
You need to tell Bit Na too.

299
00:18:09,950 --> 00:18:12,450
If this keeps up,
she'll be even more hurt later.

300
00:18:12,850 --> 00:18:14,650
No. Don't. Not yet.

301
00:18:15,583 --> 00:18:18,550
I'll meet Ji Seon
and do whatever it takes to persuade her.

302
00:18:19,650 --> 00:18:22,683
It's no use, Mom. It's over between us.

303
00:18:23,183 --> 00:18:24,983
What's over?

304
00:18:24,983 --> 00:18:27,683
Do you think you can just cut ties
between a parent and child?

305
00:18:27,950 --> 00:18:29,683
You stay out of this.

306
00:18:30,050 --> 00:18:31,883
Why do you keep getting involved
in the children's affairs?

307
00:18:33,183 --> 00:18:34,250
Seriously.

308
00:18:35,783 --> 00:18:38,083
Why's Dad acting like that to Mom?

309
00:18:38,550 --> 00:18:40,250
He's upset because of me.

310
00:18:40,983 --> 00:18:42,050
I'm sorry, Mom.

311
00:18:47,150 --> 00:18:48,883
- Hello.
- Hello, Grandma, Auntie.

312
00:18:49,750 --> 00:18:53,150
Bit Na is shining bright again today.

313
00:18:53,750 --> 00:18:55,283
Are you taking her to kindergarten today?

314
00:18:55,283 --> 00:18:56,283
Yeah.

315
00:18:57,550 --> 00:19:00,150
I heard you've been handling
all her drop-offs and pickups. Thank you.

316
00:19:00,350 --> 00:19:01,550
Come on. We're close enough.

317
00:19:02,250 --> 00:19:03,983
- See you later.
- Bye.

318
00:19:05,050 --> 00:19:06,650
Eun Hyeong, I want to come too.

319
00:19:06,750 --> 00:19:07,783
What? There's no need.

320
00:19:08,083 --> 00:19:11,350
I got all dressed up to take her
to kindergarten. It'd be a waste.

321
00:19:12,083 --> 00:19:13,250
See you later.

322
00:19:13,250 --> 00:19:16,150
Hey! Why are you butting in?

323
00:19:20,250 --> 00:19:22,950
Look at you. What a mess.

324
00:19:23,550 --> 00:19:26,650
Change into these.
I got you a shirt, underwear, and socks.

325
00:19:27,450 --> 00:19:29,183
You didn't have to. Thank you.

326
00:19:30,450 --> 00:19:33,850
What's going on?
You never stay out overnight.

327
00:19:36,050 --> 00:19:37,950
Don't tell me it's because of Manager Seo.

328
00:19:38,650 --> 00:19:42,150
Dad, I'm planning to propose to Seung Ri.

329
00:19:42,950 --> 00:19:44,850
What?

330
00:19:44,950 --> 00:19:45,950
Don't oppose it.

331
00:19:46,250 --> 00:19:49,750
If you do, I'll quit the competition
and everything else.

332
00:19:49,950 --> 00:19:52,883
You little punk.
Are you threatening me right now?

333
00:19:54,250 --> 00:19:57,650
I've told you countless times.
Seung Ri is not marriage material for you.

334
00:19:57,750 --> 00:19:58,983
That's for me to decide.

335
00:20:03,250 --> 00:20:05,350
How are you two brothers exactly the same?

336
00:20:06,283 --> 00:20:08,650
One wants an assistant's daughter,
and the other wants a chief's daughter.

337
00:20:09,650 --> 00:20:12,550
I don't care who Gyeol dates
or what he does.

338
00:20:12,550 --> 00:20:13,750
But not you.

339
00:20:14,450 --> 00:20:16,450
You're the future chairman
of Kangsu Group.

340
00:20:17,450 --> 00:20:18,550
Do you think marriage is a child's game?

341
00:20:19,350 --> 00:20:20,350
Dad.

342
00:20:20,350 --> 00:20:24,350
Don't ever bring up Seung Ri again
in front of me. Understood?

343
00:20:25,183 --> 00:20:26,183
Why you...

344
00:20:35,650 --> 00:20:36,650
Come in.

345
00:20:40,250 --> 00:20:41,250
You called for me?

346
00:20:42,250 --> 00:20:43,750
Yes, well...

347
00:20:44,550 --> 00:20:46,683
What happened
with the search for that site?

348
00:20:47,950 --> 00:20:49,350
Why haven't I heard anything?

349
00:20:50,050 --> 00:20:51,383
It's not easy.

350
00:20:51,850 --> 00:20:54,950
Finding a site that meets
all the conditions you requested...

351
00:20:56,150 --> 00:20:57,750
That's exactly why I assigned it to you.

352
00:20:57,750 --> 00:20:59,650
If it were easy, I'd do it myself.

353
00:20:59,850 --> 00:21:01,983
Why else would I have assigned it to you?

354
00:21:04,950 --> 00:21:06,083
What?

355
00:21:09,850 --> 00:21:13,216
What, are you about to say,

356
00:21:13,216 --> 00:21:15,950
"Then why did you make me your assistant?"
Is that it?

357
00:21:19,083 --> 00:21:22,683
You seem to be in a bad mood today.

358
00:21:23,350 --> 00:21:25,683
Fine. I won't push it.

359
00:21:30,050 --> 00:21:32,983
I'll put together some site options
as soon as possible.

360
00:21:33,250 --> 00:21:34,250
No.

361
00:21:34,650 --> 00:21:37,483
The final competition results
are still a long way off.

362
00:21:37,950 --> 00:21:39,850
Take your time.

363
00:21:47,183 --> 00:21:49,883
Why is he in such a bad mood too?

364
00:21:50,583 --> 00:21:51,583
Good grief.

365
00:21:52,450 --> 00:21:55,150
Wait a second. What did I just do?

366
00:21:55,550 --> 00:21:59,050
Was I being cautious of my assistant? Why?

367
00:22:00,850 --> 00:22:01,850
Seriously.

368
00:22:03,050 --> 00:22:04,850
I miss Yong Man.

369
00:22:06,183 --> 00:22:07,550
I really miss Ju Yong Man.

370
00:22:08,350 --> 00:22:12,250
What? You want me to reorganize
the entire original Joy program?

371
00:22:13,050 --> 00:22:15,983
Yes. Since you're the original developer,

372
00:22:16,250 --> 00:22:18,250
I'd like you to do it
for the good of the whole team.

373
00:22:19,150 --> 00:22:21,083
Why? Is that too much to ask?

374
00:22:21,483 --> 00:22:25,083
More importantly, each team
is already updating and developing...

375
00:22:25,083 --> 00:22:28,150
its own version of Joy.
So doing that now...

376
00:22:28,150 --> 00:22:29,883
We need the same baseline...

377
00:22:29,883 --> 00:22:32,683
to objectively compare
performance and service quality.

378
00:22:33,583 --> 00:22:35,683
The judges need the original data too...

379
00:22:35,950 --> 00:22:37,950
to clearly see the differences
between each team.

380
00:22:39,050 --> 00:22:41,850
Manager,
should I work on it together with Ms. Cho?

381
00:22:42,350 --> 00:22:43,683
It's a huge amount of material.

382
00:22:43,683 --> 00:22:44,883
No. Not you, Mr. Han.

383
00:22:45,150 --> 00:22:47,183
The original developer, Ms. Cho Eun Ae,
should handle it.

384
00:22:47,450 --> 00:22:48,750
If you split it up,
it'll only create confusion.

385
00:22:49,283 --> 00:22:50,283
Okay.

386
00:22:53,450 --> 00:22:54,550
How long will it take?

387
00:22:55,183 --> 00:22:57,650
At least three days.

388
00:22:57,750 --> 00:22:59,850
Good.
Please make sure you meet the deadline.

389
00:23:01,250 --> 00:23:03,150
Team Manager, you'll understand, right?

390
00:23:04,383 --> 00:23:07,683
Yes. If it's necessary,
there's no helping it.

391
00:23:16,850 --> 00:23:17,850
Already?

392
00:23:19,050 --> 00:23:20,650
Yes, it's okay.

393
00:23:22,550 --> 00:23:24,050
Okay.

394
00:23:26,683 --> 00:23:29,583
I didn't expect it to happen this fast.
What do I do?

395
00:23:35,683 --> 00:23:37,750
- It's Mom.
- Yes, Mom?

396
00:23:38,150 --> 00:23:39,550
Keep tonight free.

397
00:23:40,683 --> 00:23:43,383
What do you mean, why?
Because I want to have dinner with you.

398
00:23:44,150 --> 00:23:46,983
People say daughters
become your best friends as you get older.

399
00:23:48,050 --> 00:23:49,050
You're coming no matter what.

400
00:23:49,983 --> 00:23:51,483
I'll text you the details.

401
00:23:52,250 --> 00:23:54,150
Okay. See you tonight.

402
00:24:00,350 --> 00:24:02,250
You rascal. What are you looking at?

403
00:24:03,850 --> 00:24:04,983
If you run your mouth...

404
00:24:08,750 --> 00:24:11,850
At the studio, it's Witch Cho,
and at home, it's Witch Yu.

405
00:24:15,950 --> 00:24:17,850
Welcome.

406
00:24:18,883 --> 00:24:19,950
You were home?

407
00:24:19,950 --> 00:24:22,550
I heard you signed
a webtoon artist contract or something.

408
00:24:22,783 --> 00:24:25,350
Yes. I need to head to the studio
a little later.

409
00:24:26,550 --> 00:24:28,983
I was determined
to keep it a secret back then.

410
00:24:29,550 --> 00:24:30,550
Get inside.

411
00:24:31,983 --> 00:24:33,850
Okay. Have a good time.

412
00:24:36,083 --> 00:24:38,550
So what brings you here today?

413
00:24:39,783 --> 00:24:41,283
Jeong Ran, that's hurtful.

414
00:24:41,450 --> 00:24:43,683
Do we need a reason to see each other?

415
00:24:44,650 --> 00:24:45,650
Sit down.

416
00:24:50,683 --> 00:24:52,483
Are you upset with me
about something these days?

417
00:24:53,150 --> 00:24:54,950
You never show your face anymore.

418
00:24:55,283 --> 00:24:58,583
Why would I be upset?
I'm busy too, you know.

419
00:24:59,450 --> 00:25:00,450
Fine, then.

420
00:25:01,050 --> 00:25:04,850
I've spent the last few days
thinking about our relationship.

421
00:25:05,483 --> 00:25:08,583
And I've realized you're truly
my one and only best friend.

422
00:25:09,250 --> 00:25:11,783
Best friend? Not a maidservant?

423
00:25:12,350 --> 00:25:14,583
A maidservant?
Is that the name of a village?

424
00:25:15,050 --> 00:25:17,183
I'm not very familiar
with the countryside.

425
00:25:17,483 --> 00:25:19,883
You're joking, right?

426
00:25:19,950 --> 00:25:21,150
De toute façon.

427
00:25:21,650 --> 00:25:25,650
Anyway, our friendship will never change.
Got it?

428
00:25:26,950 --> 00:25:28,350
We have to become close.

429
00:25:29,050 --> 00:25:31,350
At least until the day
I figure out that safe's password.

430
00:25:34,050 --> 00:25:35,050
Why are you acting like this?

431
00:25:36,050 --> 00:25:39,683
If you're thinking about snooping around
my husband's study, forget it.

432
00:25:40,350 --> 00:25:44,083
How can you twist
someone's sincerity like that?

433
00:25:44,250 --> 00:25:46,150
I'm really not that kind of person.

434
00:25:50,950 --> 00:25:53,650
You're putting Seung Ri
on the matchmaking market?

435
00:25:54,050 --> 00:25:56,183
Yes. Why not?

436
00:25:56,850 --> 00:25:57,850
My Seung Ri...

437
00:25:58,783 --> 00:26:01,750
is going to meet a fine man
and get married soon.

438
00:26:02,350 --> 00:26:03,383
Just wait and see.

439
00:26:04,450 --> 00:26:07,750
That's a great idea.
You should've done it sooner.

440
00:26:08,050 --> 00:26:10,383
- Since our Min Ho could never...
- If you don't want to ruin things,

441
00:26:11,750 --> 00:26:14,683
don't tell Min Ho. Understood?

442
00:26:15,250 --> 00:26:16,383
Of course.

443
00:26:17,183 --> 00:26:20,050
If anything, merci beaucoup.

444
00:26:28,550 --> 00:26:29,550
Hey, Seung Wu.

445
00:26:31,250 --> 00:26:32,250
What?

446
00:26:55,383 --> 00:26:56,850
Where are you? I'm already here.

447
00:26:58,850 --> 00:27:01,250
What? A blind date? What do you...

448
00:27:01,883 --> 00:27:02,950
Mom!

449
00:27:09,750 --> 00:27:11,250
Are you Ms. Seo Seung Ri?

450
00:27:11,650 --> 00:27:13,950
Sorry? Yes.

451
00:27:20,450 --> 00:27:22,750
Are you here for a blind date?

452
00:27:23,650 --> 00:27:24,650
Yes.

453
00:27:26,650 --> 00:27:29,050
Actually, my mom told me
we were just having dinner together.

454
00:27:29,483 --> 00:27:31,150
I had no idea
this was one of those meetings.

455
00:27:31,150 --> 00:27:32,883
I'm sorry. Then I'll...

456
00:27:33,450 --> 00:27:34,450
Hey.

457
00:27:35,083 --> 00:27:37,050
I paid 10,000 dollars
just for the membership fee.

458
00:27:37,550 --> 00:27:38,750
You can't just leave like this.

459
00:27:51,050 --> 00:27:52,950
Sorry, Seung Ri.
I'm really late, aren't I?

460
00:27:57,183 --> 00:27:58,683
Who are you?

461
00:27:58,750 --> 00:27:59,883
Nice to meet you.

462
00:28:00,650 --> 00:28:03,350
I'm Ko Min Ho, Seung Ri's boyfriend.

463
00:28:05,083 --> 00:28:06,083
What?

464
00:28:20,550 --> 00:28:22,083
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
